Parts of‘ esse,' other than present indicative and infinitive‚ are omitted, especially in relative or dependent clauses, as quod peditum (sc. fuit), interfecit, xiv 32, 6; qua proximum . . . Armenios petivit, xv 12, 1. The subjunctive of this verb is also freely omitted when another subjunctive follows, and in oratio obliqua, as xiii 55, 5. Note also omission of ‘ fuisse ’ after a future participle, xv 16, 1; xv 24, 33 xv 67, 1.
